window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Looking for a brilliant best-selling crime mystery with great detectives?&nbsp;</p> <p>Detectives Calladine and Bayliss face a vicious serial killer in a mystery with a shocking ending.&nbsp;</p> <p>A woman’s body is found in a disused church, a homemade stuffed toy by her side. The victim had been dumped there months ago. The crime has the hallmarks of 20-year-old case whose alleged perpetrator is in prison.&nbsp;</p> <p>Detective Ruth Bayliss must work out whether a serial killer has returned, or if a new killer is just taunting the police.&nbsp;</p> <p>Her partner DI Tom Calladine faces the fight of his life to clear his name of corruption accusations. And then things go from bad to worse for Calladine....&nbsp;</p> <p>With the team under massive pressure and drugs flooding the streets, another gruesomely presented body is found.&nbsp;</p> <p>In an ending with a huge twist, the detectives must unpick decades’ old lies before anyone else dies.&nbsp;</p> <p>If you like Angela Marsons, Rachel Abbott, Mel Sherratt, Ruth Rendell or Mark Billingham, you will enjoy this exciting new crime fiction writer.&nbsp;</p>"; 
